Description: Minature pottery conical transport amphora (?), without handles, neck broken and missing, traces of a whitish deposit in places. Before firing, a bird facing to the left, with a tripartie tail, has been carved on one side between the shoulder and the base
Bibliographic references: Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.106, p.218, pl.60)
